  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding Requirement mandates controlled-experiment verification of hemolysis predictions across all five flow-speed operating points. The supporting validation activity — a multi-site observational study drawing on clinical registry data and post-market surveillance records — is cited extensively in the rationale and described as providing equivalent empirical grounding. Reviewers are directed to the breadth of the observational dataset (n=312 device-patient pairs, 18-month follow-up, three clinical sites) as evidence of rigorous empirical support. The structured activityType field, however, records 'observational-study', which does not satisfy the 'controlled-experiment' requirement. The inference link from evidence to requirement is thereby undercut (W-AR-03).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
